## 9. Emotion-to-Tone Routing

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    classDef emo fill:#3498DB,stroke:#1A5276,color:#fff
    classDef tone fill:#E67E22,stroke:#784212,color:#fff
    classDef resp fill:#27AE60,stroke:#145A32,color:#fff

    JOY2["Joy"]:::emo --> ENT["Enthusiastic Tone"]:::tone
    SAD2["Sadness"]:::emo --> SUP["Supportive Tone"]:::tone
    ANG2["Anger"]:::emo --> SUP
    FEA2["Fear"]:::emo --> SUP
    SUR2["Surprise"]:::emo --> CLA["Clarifying Tone"]:::tone
    DIS2["Disgust"]:::emo --> NEU2["Neutral Tone"]:::tone
    NEU3["Neutral"]:::emo --> NEU2
    LOW["Low Confidence < 0.5"]:::emo --> NEU2

    ENT --> R1["Warm enthusiastic reply\nmax 100 tokens"]:::resp
    SUP --> R2["Empathetic validating reply\nmax 120-140 tokens"]:::resp
    CLA --> R3["Exploratory questioning reply\nmax 150 tokens"]:::resp
    NEU2 --> R4["Balanced helpful reply\nmax 150 tokens"]:::resp
```

